                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Merry</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bacon acknowledges the receipt of Mr. Merry’s telegram of the 10th. Directs
                    Mr. Merry to continue to use his good offices to prevent war if possible. Mr.
                    Bacon informs Mr. Merry that a cablegram has been sent to Ambassador Thompson
                    and hopes for the cooperation and moral support of the Government of Mexico. The
                        <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> has been ordered to go to the coast of
                    Salvador and communicate with Mr. Merry.</p>
                <p>Mr. Bacon directs Mr. Merry to exercise great care so as not to encroach upon the
                    sovereign rights in any way.)</p>
            </div>
